__DESCRIPTION__

Larry Wall's background in linguistics helped him to create a programming language
that borrows bits from other languages, much like English.

BigThink <a href="http://bigthink.com/larrywall">interview with Larry Wall</a>.
<p>
In this part he answers the questions:

<h2>Did your study of linguistics play a role in Perl's development?</h2>

and

<h2>How are human languages and programming languages similar?</h2>

